race.description: Construction Control Country Boosted Mdn Hcp
race.comment: PINK LAMBORGHINI (3) has switched from a Victorian yard on a 200-day return. She races forward and brings strong numbers from Pakenham and Geelong. Cahill's booking suggests she's pleasing, and she's a strong chance to break through. TIS NO MAN (2) debuts for a sharp local barn with two trials under the saddle. Owen sticks from the latest and that's a lead. Has an awkward gate, but expect him to race boldly. ARTFUL LADY (7) debuts for Canberra's top yard and she was beaten 1.6L in a recent Goulburn trial. She also draws out but looks to have good ability and is ready to go. ZIPPY ARGENTO (5) was in the market at Wagga Riverside on debut but didn't get into it from a wide barrier. Resumes today and has the inside gate and the blinkers on for the first time. The local needs to be kept safe.
